h - Cursor - move cursor left
j - Cursor - move cursor down
k - Cursor - move cursor up
l - Cursor - move cursor right
w - Cursor - jump forwards to the start of a word
W - Cursor - jump forwards to the start of a word (words can contain punctuation)
e - Cursor - jump forwards to the end of a word
E - Cursor - jump forwards to the end of a word (words can contain punctuation)
b - Cursor - jump backwards to the start of a word
B - Cursor - jump backwards to the start of a word (words can contain punctuation)
0 - Cursor - jump to the start of the line
^ - Cursor - jump to the first non-blank character of the line
$ - Cursor - jump to the end of the line
G - Cursor - go to the last line of the document
5G - Cursor - go to line 5
i - Insert - insert before the cursor
I - Insert - insert at the beginning of the line
a - Insert - insert (append) after the cursor
A - Insert - insert (append) at the end of the line
o - Insert - append (open) a new line below the current line
O - Insert - append (open) a new line above the current line
ea - Insert - insert (append) at the end of the word
Esc - Insert - exit insert mode
r - Editing - replace a single character
J - Editing - join line below to the current one
cc - Editing - change (replace) entire line
cw - Editing - change (replace) to the end of the word
c$ - Editing - change (replace) to the end of the line
s - Editing - delete character and substitute text
S - Editing - delete line and substitute text (same as cc)
xp - Editing - transpose two letters (delete and paste)
u - Editing - undo
Ctrl + r - Editing - redo
. - Editing - repeat last command
v - Visual - start visual mode, mark lines, then do a command (like y-yank)
V - Visual - start linewise visual mode
o - Visual - move to other end of marked area
Ctrl + v - Visual - start visual block mode
O - Visual - move to other corner of block
aw - Visual - mark a word
ab - Visual - a block with ()
aB - Visual - a block with {}
ib - Visual - inner block with ()
iB - Visual - inner block with {}
Esc - Visual - exit visual mode
> - Visual - shift text right
< - Visual - shift text left
y - Visual - yank (copy) marked text
d - Visual - delete marked text
~ - Visual - switch case
yy - Cut and Paste - yank (copy) a line
2yy - Cut and Paste - yank (copy) 2 lines
yw - Cut and Paste - yank (copy) word
y$ - Cut and Paste - yank (copy) to end of line
p - Cut and Paste - put (paste) the clipboard after cursor
P - Cut and Paste - put (paste) before cursor
dd - Cut and Paste - delete (cut) a line
2dd - Cut and Paste - delete (cut) 2 lines
dw - Cut and Paste - delete (cut) word
D - Cut and Paste - delete (cut) to the end of the line
d$ - Cut and Paste - delete (cut) to the end of the line
x - Cut and Paste - delete (cut) character
:w- Exiting - write (save) the file, but don't exit
:wq or :x or ZZ - Exiting- write (save) and quit
:q - Exiting- quit (fails if there are unsaved changes)
:q! or ZQ - Exiting- quit and throw away unsaved changes
/pattern - Search and Replace - search for pattern
?pattern - Search and Replace- search backward for pattern
n - Search and Replace- repeat search in same direction
N - Search and Replace- repeat search in opposite direction
:%s/old/new/g - Search and Replace- replace all old with new throughout file
:%s/old/new/gc - Search and Replace- replace all old with new throughout file with confirmations
:tabnew filename or :tabn filename - Tabs - open a file in a new tab
Ctrl + wT - Tabs- move the current split window into its own tab
gt or :tabnext or :tabn - Tabs- move to the next tab
gT or :tabprev or :tabp - Tabs - move to the previous tab
#gt - Tabs - move to tab number #
:tabmove # - Tabs - move current tab to the #th position (indexed from 0)
:tabclose or :tabc - Tabs - close the current tab and all its windows
:tabonly or :tabo - Tabs - close all tabs except for the current one
:e filename - Multi Files - edit a file in a new buffer
:bnext or :bn - Multi Files - go to the next buffer
:bprev or :bp - Multi Files - go to the previous buffer
:bd - Multi Files - delete a buffer (close a file)
:sp filename - Multi Files - open a file in a new buffer and split window
:vsp filename - Multi Files - open a file in a new buffer and vertically split window
Ctrl + ws - Multi Files - split window
Ctrl + ww - Multi Files - switch windows
Ctrl + wq - Multi Files - quit a window
Ctrl + wv - Multi Files - split window vertically
Ctrl + wh - Multi Files - move cursor to the left window (vertical split)
Ctrl + wl - Multi Files - move cursor to the right window (vertical split)
Ctrl + wj - Multi Files - move cursor to the window below (horizontal split)
Ctrl + wk - Multi Files - move cursor to the window above (horizontal split)
